pullRequest.body:
Rework some definitions and theorems related to separation of points in measurable spaces. Notably added `SeparatesPoints`, a typeclass recording that a measurable space separates points. This is closely related to `MeasurableSingletonClass` and `HasCountableSeparating on _ MeasurableSet`, and supporting lemmas/instances linking them are included.

The goal was to add `borelSpace_secondCountableTopology_t4_of_countablyGenerated` and `opensMeasurableSpace_secondCountableTopology_t4_of_hasCountableSeparatingOn`. In future PRs these will be used to reduce statements about measurability with the assumptions such as `BorelSpace/OpensMeasurableSpace`, `SecondCountableTopology` etc. to those whose assumptions are only `CountableGenerated` or `HasCountableSeparatingOn` etc.

Also separated part of `Topology/Instances/Discrete` into a new file, `Topology/Instances/Countable`. `BorelSpace/Basic` is not allowed to import the former because of the `assert_not_exists NormedSpace` in `MeasureTheory/Integral/Lebesgue.lean`. 


---
